text: Lincoln County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming. As of the 2020 census, 19,581 people lived there. Its county seat is Kemmerer. Its western border abuts the east border of the state of Utah. == History == Lincoln County was created on February 21, 1911. The county was named for Abraham Lincoln, 16th President of the United States. == Geography == According to the US Census Bureau, the county has a total area of , of which is land and (0.5%) is water. === Bordering counties === * Teton County – north * Sublette County – northeast * Sweetwater County – east * Uinta County – south * Rich County, Utah – southwest * Bear Lake County, Idaho – west * Caribou County, Idaho – northwest * Bonneville County, Idaho – northwest == Communities == === City === * Kemmerer (county seat) === Towns === * Afton * Alpine * Cokeville * Diamondville * La Barge * Opal * Star Valley Ranch * Thayne === Census- designated places === * Alpine Northeast * Alpine Northwest * Auburn * Bedford * Etna * Fairview * Fontenelle * Freedom * Grover * Nordic * Oakley * Osmond * Smoot * Taylor * Turnerville === Unincorporated communities === * Alpine Junction * Border Junction * Frontier * Hamsfork * Sage == References == == Other websites == * Lincoln County, Wyoming official website * Star Valley Wyoming in Lincoln County Category:Wyoming counties Category:1911 establishments in Wyoming
